 Contract workers employed by Optimum Coal Mine came together at the mine entrance in protest, claiming that it has now been three months since they have not received any pay. The N11 was littered with large rocks, burning logs and tyres. A truck was forced to stop in the middle of the road and dump its load of sand on the N11. The N11 was blocked with logs, large rocks and a truck which dumped a load of sand in the middle of the road.  Also read: #TrafficUpdate: N11 and main road to Pullenshope closed Protesters told www.mobserver.co.za that the ANC Minister of Mineral Resources, Mr Gwede Mantashe, spoke to them a month ago, yet nothing has been done since. “We have not been paid for three months, we have not been paid our U.I.F and pension funds. We have recently engaged with the Business Rescue Practitioners but until now, there has been no change,” Mr Mahlanga told www.mobserver.co.za. •Police are currently at the scene and controlling the situation. The N11 is open and traffic is being navigated around the obstacles, however, the road going to Optimum is still blocked.    Dullstroom farm attack trial postponed VIDEO: Dance group brings joy to residents Middelburg weekly weather forecast Pay or use ‘The road where death lives’  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za